onaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Jzonn quickly turns around with a start.  &quot;Ahh good.  You're here.  I have some ideas on how to help this trip.  We should probably talk about them on the boat ride.  We'll also need both our limited healing abilities, I'm sure.&quot;  Jzonn turns to Casidy, &quot;Are we waiting on anyone else?&quot; <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uqwiktaveren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qwik Ta veren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/24/01 4:21:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> reluctantly Qwik walks over to Jzonn ... my apologies .. i wont be joining you as i had planned . Things have ... changed.  I have some other things i must attend to so i wish you all well and take care. *giving the group one last look over , releasing a sigh of dissapointment Qwik turns and heads for the door*<br>
 <p>Qwik Ta`veren Monk of the Wheel and loyal student of Master Chopp Styxx "THE PATTERN WILL SERVE MY WILL!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucrydeeossiriand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crydee Ossiriand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/24/01 10:52:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Crydee frowns briefly. He spent the last hour bored watching Caisdy and Febreeza chatting, just wondering what they were saying, while they waited for Jzonn to show up. Crydee notices that Jzonn's lips also move silently, now that Crydee revealed himself. More groupsay talk... Never being the sort to stay where he isn't welcome, Crydee decides to make an exit.<br>
<br>
"Looks like you don't really need me for your trip, so I'll be on my way."<br>
<br>
Crydee camoflages himself and dashes off to the nearest druid portal.<br>
<br>
<br>
/ooc I'm not going to be able to get online much next week, so I'm yanking Crydee out of the story for now. No need to hold things up waiting for me.<br>
<br>
 <p><P><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="2"><B>Crydee Ossiriand</B><BR>
<FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="1">The Questing Ranger on Ayonae Ro<BR>
<A HREF="http://monsterweb.org">http://monsterweb.org</A><BR>
<BR>
Through your will has balance returned. Your deeds, your work for the good of all, will be remembered by anyone who walks beneath the canopy of a forest or roams the plains. Continue your vigil over nature's balance, Crydee.</FONT></P>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufebreeza.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Febreeza</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/28/01 5:53:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Febreeza watches Qwik and Crydee taking their leave quite abruptly, and looks at Jzonn.<br>
<br>
&quot;You planning on jumping ship too?  Or are you in this for the long haul?  Personally, I am in this till we finish, but if we don't get going soon we are going to miss our deadline.&quot;<br>
<br>
Looks to Casidy to see if she is ready to head for the dock.  Then turns away and heads toward where she heard this new dock was. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/28/01 7:09:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest:  A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> &quot;Aye.  I'm in for the long haul&quot;, Jzonn answers to Febreeza.  He shakes his head as he watches Crydee and Qwik each walk away.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> This will prove to be interesting.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Gently pulling on Casidy's arm, she moves along after Febreeza and they journey further into the passage way of the mountain and into the northern portion of the Ro desert. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucrydeeossiriand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crydee Ossiriand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/1/01 5:33:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> /ooc Pfft. I was offline for days while waiting for my new PC. Didn't want to tie things up.<br>
<br>
<br>
Crydee finishes up what business he had elsewhere and stops by the Shopping District in East Commons several days later. He notices that Casidy, Febreeza and Jzonn are still there. Crydee wanders by and waves hellp.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usirtaino.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SirTainO</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/3/01 10:55:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jollyjokers.com/images/pally.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Having watched the scene for a while Taino decides to join the group as asked. He feels honored and enjoys the taste of the salty air in his nose as they move to the dock in the Northern Desert of Ro.<br>
<br>
It was not hard to find since this Gnome Pirate is shouting and advertising his ship over to the cold side like a new shampoo product line or the Freeport Militia on the search of new Soldiers. <br>
<br>
The all sit down and wait for the Boat to come. <br>
He looks at Febreeza and nods with a smile playing around his lips. He feels much respect for this little gnome warrioress. She showed very strict but good leadership in other battles with him already. Certainly a great partner for this trip. He feels good and safe.<br>
The young Bard is exactly the way he expected her to be. Young, wild and always flirting around. She never can stand still. She has still much to learn and to get her wild temper under control if the situation asks for it. But she performs well and got the best teacher of all. After all we all are happy to have some entertainment and music. The other members Taino has never seen before. <br>
There is no way to judge them yet, but they seem to make up a nice group all together. <br>
The bard keeps peeking over to the Ranger. The also seem to know eachother well. The Bard is always peeking over to all Rangers, so Taino is not sure about it. But its not his business anyways. <br>
<br>
"The ship comes, the ship comes"<br>
The bard jumps up and points over to the horizon.<br>
Its not really what a Paladin would call a ship. Some old pieces of wood nailed to something that swims. <br>
Taino takes Febreezas hand and guides her on the ship, letting her get aboard first. Not that a warrioress would need this "help" but thats the little gestures that are asked and appropriate from a Paladin. <br>
<br>
As he wanted to help the Bard he saw her already standing on the boat singing a happy seafarer's Tune.<br>
<br>
We sit down and the pieces of wood find their way over to colder water and weather. Having the Bard to sing and play and to share a few Eleven Wines turns the journey on this wreck into a welcome ride where everyone is in a good mood and gets to know eachother a little better.<br>
<br>
<br>
_______________________________<br>
Magic Hands write on the sky:<br>
LOADING PLEASE WAIT...<br>
You have entered Iceclad Ocean.<br>
You have formed the Group.<br>
_______________________________<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/3/01 9:01:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.honestevil.com/deleted_roster/hail_head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> The air was fridge and cold.<br>
<br>
Casidy wrapped her arms deep into her cloak and breathed out a note on the air.<br>
<br>
The note turned to popsicles before her. Turning in her song book, she found just the right tune.<br>
<br>
Casidy began to sing a song of warmth to warm the air around her friends.<br>
<br>
She was already feeling a bit warmer.<br>
<br>
Yes this wouldn't be so bad, true this boat was tiny... alot smaller than she had expected, but she was in good company.<br>
<br>
As she finished the first verse of her song, she leaned over to Jzonn "Might I have a bit of the wine to warm my inside as the song has warmed my hands?"<br>
<br>
Surveying her companions she smiled, this would be a long journey but a fun one indeed.<br>
 <p><br><b><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2 COLOR="#6699cc">
---------------------------<br>
 Silent, Deadly         <br>
 Yeah, Right                  <br>
---------------------------<br>
<br>
~ Casidy Noteworthy</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufebreeza.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Febreeza</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/4/01 12:42:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Febreeza smiles fondly at the young Paladin, allowing for his gallant gestures, for she knows they are meant respectfully.<br>
<br>
Watching the little boat of boards and barrels come upon an island, the Gnome Pirate standing on the beach yells for everyone to hop off before the boat takes off again.  She leaps into the water and swims to shore.<br>
<br>
Jzonn leads the group across the island to a large dock that sticks out into the water.  And the group once again waits as Jzonn explains that there is a larger boat that will complete the trip.<br>
<br>
She listens closely as he begins telling the group some of the things that they might expect to see on this trip.  Warning of dangers to watch out for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/4/01 3:50:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Jzonn begins to rummage search for the particular pack with the wine.  Finding it, he pulls out a bottle of a red and checks the label.  &quot;This is from a vinyard north of Felwithe.  It's not the best region for wine grapes, but the morning dew used in the cleasing process brings out its unique flavor.  One of the better years too.&quot;  Removing the cork, Jzonn hand the bottle to Casidy.  &quot;I'm afraid we'll have to forgo the niceties of a glass.&quot;<br>
<br>
Waiting for the strange boat of the Gnomes, Icebreaker, Jzonn relays what information he knows about the frozen land.  Looking into the sky, he senses a change in the coming weather.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I hope this is just a passing sea squall.  We do not need a trip full of nasty weather.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;...and if all goes well, we'll be camoflaguing ourselves to avoid any unpleasant encounters.  Perhaps a bit boring, but we'll make it to the Coldain city within the time frames allowed.&quot; <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#3A6EA5">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Final Destiny&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#cfcfcf">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucrydeeossiriand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crydee Ossiriand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/4/01 4:02:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Crydee watches as everyone leaves without him and takes note that they enbark on the boat to Velious. The ranger wasn't found of boat trips and had a tendancy to feel ill on any that were lengthy. He always looked for ways out of taking boats.<br>
<br>
*Hmm... since I wasn't really part of their group nor invited to come along, Casidy's 'no teleport' rule shouldn't apply to me. Maybe she'll recruit my help after she takes her boat ride.*<br>
<br>
Crydee grins at the thought of not having to take a boat. He talks briefly with a druid, who ports him to Iceclad Ocean. Crydee runs along the snow pickup up white flowers that grow up out of the ice. By the time he gets to the docks, he has a dozen or so of them.<br>
<br>
Crydee sits at the dock. He waits for the boat to show up. He waits even more for Casidy...<br>
 <p><P><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="2"><B>Crydee Ossiriand</B><BR>
<FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="1">The Questing Ranger on Ayonae Ro<BR>
<A HREF="http://monsterweb.org">http://monsterweb.org</A><BR>
<BR>
Through your will has balance returned. Your deeds, your work for the good of all, will be remembered by anyone who walks beneath the canopy of a forest or roams the plains. Continue your vigil over nature's balance, Crydee.</FONT></P>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukristav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kristav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/5/01 3:45:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard's Quest: A New Beginning</span><hr size=1> Meanwhile...<br>
<br>
&quot;What was I thinking,&quot; whimpered Kristav, yet again.  It was probably the fifth time he had uttered those words in the past hour, with his only other phrase being, &quot;By the gods, it's cold here.&quot;  For the most part, the black-armored gnomes were no help, preferring to sit around in their (warm and comfortable) tents practicing their pirate speak.<br>
<br>
&quot;HARR!&quot; shouted one, and a few more piped up with &quot;Arr!&quot; and &quot;Harr!&quot; and &quot;Ni!&quot;  Kristav shuddered, trying to pull his cloak tighter around his shoulders and being reminded, yet again, that he didn't have a cloak.<br>
<br>
&quot;STUPID DWARF!&quot; he shouted, and then blushed a bright red as he apologetically explained to the dwarf sitting nearby that, no, sir, it wasn't actually him he was shouting at and, yes, sir, he WAS training to be a bard, but no, sir, he wasn't really smart enough to be doing anything useful, and yes, sir, whatever you say, sir...<br>
<br>
As he desperately pleaded not to be used in an experiment in how long it would take a wood elf to dig himself a new underground home in the frozen mountainside, he tried to think back to his reasons for travelling to Velious.  After all, it wasn't as if he had much need to visit these new lands - there were still plenty of areas on Antonica which he hadn't visited, and he'd never been to Erud or Kunark - both nice warm places.  And if it was snow he had wanted, he could have simply gone to visit Halas.<br>
<br>
Then he remembered.  Ruka.  Lovely Ruka, his childhood friend.  They had grown up together, insomuch as two wood elves, born ten years apart, one practically a princess as wood elves treat such things and the other, well, Kristav, could grow up together.  He had been there for much of her young training, listening to her problems, comforting her in times of need, making her laugh, and, unfortunately, remembering that old adage of &quot;listening to your heart&quot; and actually SAYING IT OUT LOUD, of all things, advice which she took completely and used as an excuse to leave wood elf society and take up wandering.<br>
<br>
Not that wandering was a bad thing, but he had always kind of hoped and assumed that maybe, just maybe... well, that she would end up wandering with him.  Which was kind of what he had in mind when he advised her to listen to her heart.<br>
<br>
Fortunately, there hadn't been much backlash from that little error, mostly because once his parents had found out, they decided that right now would be a perfect chance to start his new career, in the Commonlands outside Freeport, where he trained under the master bard, Teuvian, in his tavern.  Except, of course, that Teuvian had retired from the adventuring life and used to, in private, whine about what a horrible thing it was, and how much happier he was having hung up his sword and settled down with his wife, Lildara.<br>
<br>
Then the Dwarf had come into the tavern.  That paladin dwarf, the one who travelled with Ruka.  Kristav had recognised him almost immediately, and had barraged him with questions about Ruka, how she was doing, and what would impress her into coming back and meeting up with her childhood friend.<br>
<br>
Tragically, he realised as he searched the horizon for the return of the Icebreaker, tragically, it had never registered in his mind at the time that &quot;Why don't you go to Velious and try and get yourself eaten by a Snow Cougar&quot; might have been somewhat a sarcastic comment...<br>
<br>
